:58,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظَلَّ","root":"ظلل","pos":"V","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":23},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27587"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shadow, shade"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reflection"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shady garden"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paradise"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"protection, help, assistance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dark cloud"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"darkness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"night"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"phantom, specter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cover, lid, scabbard"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shape, figure, person"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the Sultan (as shadow of God on Earth)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"greatness, sublimity, distinction, eminence, rareness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power, night"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"colors of the day, shades of color, bloom of youth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"heat of summer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fringe, hairy side of a cloth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trace"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tangent (symbol: ظا, ظل)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to remain, to persist, to maintain","tags":["copulative"],"examples":[{"text":"ظَلَّ صَامِتًا","english":"He remained silent."},{"text":"ظَلَّ عَلَى مَوْقِفِهِ","english":"He maintained his point of view. [= stayed in the place he was standing]"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to keep doing, to do constantly, to persist in, to remain","examples":[{"text":"يَظَلُّ يَتْبَعُهَا","english":"He keeps following her."},{"text":"ظَلُّوا جَالِسِينَ","english":"They remained sitting."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ظَلَّ (ẓalla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṯ̣ill- (“shadow”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒄑𒈪 (ṣillum), Ugaritic 𐎑𐎍 (ẓl) and Biblical Hebrew צל (ṣel)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27587","headword_ar":"ظَلَّ","root":"Zl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZil~u","text_ar":"يَظِلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlapN","text_ar":"ظِلَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb, K,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, O, Msb, K,) [and accord. to SM"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalalotu","text_ar":"ظَلَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, for he says that] the verb is of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaEa","text_ar":"مَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEiba","text_ar":"تَعِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalotu","text_ar":"ظَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, * M, O, K,) likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasotu","text_ar":"لَسْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, *) formed by rejecting the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zilotu","text_ar":"ظِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is [also] originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, T, M, O, K,) formed by transferring to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the vowel of the rejected"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, T, M, O,) anomalously, (Sb, M,) the latter of the dial. of the people of El-Hijáz; (T;) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZal~u","text_ar":"يَظَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * M, O, * Msb, K;) imperative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZolalo","text_ar":"اِظْلَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalo","text_ar":"ظَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T) [and it is implied in the M voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qar~a","text_ar":"قَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"that one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZolilo","text_ar":"اِظْلِلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zilo","text_ar":"ظِلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which indicates that the aor. is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZil~u","text_ar":"يَظِلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this requires confirmation, which I have not anywhere found]; inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuluwlN","text_ar":"ظُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~N","text_ar":"ظَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (thus also in a copy of the M; [but this I think doubtful;]) accord. to Lth, (T,) or Kh, (Msb,) [i. e. accord. to the author of the 'Eyn,] is said only of a thing that is done in the day, or daytimes; (T, S, M, O, Msb;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAta","text_ar":"بَاتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabiytu","text_ar":"يَبِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is said only of a thing that is done in the night: (T:) it is an incomplete [i. e. a non-attributive] verb, relating to a time in which is a shade from the sun, from morning to evening, or from sunrise to sunset: (Esh-Shiháb, TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN nahaArahu SaAy^imFA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ نَهَارَهُ صَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was during his day fasting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed his day fasting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Lth, T:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a nahaArahu yafoEalu ka*aA","text_ar":"ظَلَّ نَهَارَهُ يَفْعَلُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during, his day doing such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed his day doing such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu A^aEomalu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ اَعْمَلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was in the day"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daytime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed the day, doing such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did such a thing in the day"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daytime."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb. *) In the saying of 'Antarah,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaqado A^abiytu EalaY AlT~awaY waA^aZal~uhu\n                      \n                     \n                        Hat~aY A^anaAla bihi kariyma AlmaA^okali"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily I pass the night in hunger, and I pass the day in it, that I may attain thereby plentiful eating"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZal~uhu","text_ar":"اَظَلُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZal~u","text_ar":"اَظَلُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) And accord. to some, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolahu","text_ar":"لَيْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in poetry; (M, K, TA;) so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a layolahu yafoEalu ka*aA","text_ar":"ظَلَّ لَيْلَهُ يَفْعَلُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during, his night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed his night, doing such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but it is said that in this case the verb has the meaning next following. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, became;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra","text_ar":"صَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib, TA:) being in this sense likewise an incomplete [i. e. a non-attributive] verb, divested of that meaning of time which it radically denotes; as in the phrase in the Kur [xvi. 60 and xliii. 16],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a wajohuhu musowad~FA","text_ar":"ظَلَّ وَجْهُهُ مُسْوَدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His face becomes black"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says Ibn-Málik: (TA:) or this may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his face continues all the day black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xvi. 60:) and one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEalu ka*aA","text_ar":"يَفْعَلُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He continued doing such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this too is mentioned by Ibn-Málik, and is of the dial. of the people of Syria. (TA.) ―         -b3-  It is also a complete [i. e. an attributive] verb as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, continued;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is said in the Expos. of the “ Shifè, ” and by Ibn-Málik; and, as Ibn-Málik likewise says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","Msb","K","S","O","TA","Sb","Lth"]}]}}